Rick Moran does not run paranormal Systems, ron Ricketts does.

Rick Moran runs a non-profit paranormal research site that studied the 
Mini-Box

Kathy
----- Original Message ----- 
From: &quot;bhali333&quot; &lt;paranormalinvestigating@...&gt;
To: &lt;EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com&gt;
Sent: Tuesday, April 15, 2008 4:02 PM
Subject: [EVP-ITC] My Ebay Price For The Mini-Box


&gt; Hi everyone,
&gt;
&gt; A few people have seen my ebay listing and commented about the price
&gt; listed.
&gt;
&gt; Ebay will not allow you to change a description after the item has
&gt; been listed. They do however allow you to add and amending statement.
&gt;
&gt; Which I have done In Big Bold Red Letters, the price listing was a
&gt; mistake. I am certainly not trying to misrepresent the item or make a
&gt; profit on it.
&gt;
&gt; I have also lowered the reserve price on it as a result of the
&gt; mistake.
&gt; Believe me I will be taking a loss on the box.
&gt;
&gt; I have already sent my apologies to Rick Moran from Paranormal
&gt; systems.
&gt;
&gt; And now extend my apologies for the mistake to anyone that was
&gt; interested in it.
&gt;
&gt; The reason for selling the MB was not the money, it was the guilt of
&gt; having this excellent piece of equipment go without the attention it
&gt; deserves. And the hopes that someone or some group can utilize it
&gt; more than myself.
&gt;
&gt; But I could not as much as I would have liked to, give it away.
&gt; My intention was to get back at least a decent amount of my
&gt; investment.
&gt;
&gt; I hope no one gets the wrong idea and thinks ill of me.
&gt;
&gt; Bruce
